    <h2><center>Course Overview</center></h2>
    <p>
        <center>
            Level 3 Access to Higher Education courses are designed to enable mature learners (19+) 
            who have been out of education to gain the qualifications, academic skills and knowledge necessary 
            to progress on to university-level study in the field of computing and digital studies. 
            The diploma is studied full-time over one year. You will be required to attend college lectures and 
            seminars for a minimum of two and a half days per week.
        </center>
    </p>
    <h2><center>Course Content</center></h2>
    <p><center>This Digital pathway includes: Web Development, Programming, IT Application skills, Cyber Security, 
                Object Oriented Programming, Games Programming, Academic Writing and 
                study skills to prepare you for university.
    </center></p>
    <p></p>
    <h2><center>Entry Requirement</center></h2>
    <p>
        <center>
            You will need a Grade C/4 in GCSE English and GCSE Maths. 
            *If applicants have Grade D/3 you will be required to sit GCSE Maths alongside your studies. 
            You will also need to pass an internal interview and Maths and English screening to ascertain your knowledge level. 
            Any relevant work experience will also be taken in to consideration.
        </center>
    </p>
    <h2><center>Progression and Cost</center></h2>
    <p>
